## Implementation Guide

### Data Sources

#### Dashcam Detail
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/`
- **Fields Used**:
  - `id` - Dashcam ID
  - `device_id` - Device identifier
  - `vehicle` - Associated vehicle (ID)
  - `firmware_version` - Current firmware version
  - `is_active` - Active status
  - `last_streamed_at` - Last stream timestamp
  - `api_key` - API key for device authentication (admin-only)
  - `created_at` - Creation timestamp

#### Vehicle Information
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/vehicles/{id}/` (where id is from dashcam.vehicle)
- **Fields Used**: Vehicle details like make, model, VIN, etc.

#### KPI Cards
- **Firmware**: Current firmware version
- **Last Streamed**: Time since last stream or "Live" if streaming
- **API Key Created**: When the API key was created/refreshed
- **Signal Strength**: Connection quality (if available)

### Live Stream Section
- **WebSocket Endpoint**: `ws://stream/dashcam/{id}/` (hypothetical)
- **Alternative**: HTTP streaming via `GET /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/stream/`
- **Controls**:
  - Play/Pause: Start/stop video playback
  - Record: Initiate recording
  - Snapshot: Capture still image
  - Full Screen: Expand video to full screen
- **Stream URL**: Displayed for reference/debugging purposes

### Recent Recordings Section
- **API Endpoint**: `GET /api/fleet/video-segments/?dashcam={id}&limit=3`
- **Fields Used**:
  - Date
  - Start/End times
  - Duration
  - File size
- **View Action**: Opens video player modal or navigates to recording detail page

### Action Buttons
- **Edit**:
  - **API**: `PUT /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Update endpoint in base endpoints section
  
- **Start Stream**:
  - **API**: Custom implementation or WebSocket connection

- **Reset**:
  - **API**: Custom implementation
  - **Purpose**: Restart the device software

- **Factory Reset**:
  - **API**: Custom implementation
  - **Purpose**: Reset device to factory settings (more drastic than simple reset)

- **Delete**:
  - **API**: `DELETE /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Delete endpoint in base endpoints section

- **Refresh API Key** (in device details section):
  - **API**: `POST /api/fleet/dashcams/refresh_api_key/`
  - **Request Body**: `{ "selected_records": [id] }`
  - **Documentation Reference**: Documented refresh_api_key endpoint

### API Alignment
All endpoints and fields used in this design match the documentation in dashcams.md:
- `GET /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/` - Get dashcam details
- `PUT /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/` - Update dashcam
- `DELETE /api/fleet/dashcams/{id}/` - Delete dashcam
- `POST /api/fleet/dashcams/refresh_api_key/` - Refresh API key
- `GET /api/fleet/video-segments/?dashcam={id}` - Get dashcam recordings
- `GET /api/fleet/vehicles/{id}/` - Get vehicle details
